# USB on the left USB-C port (see patches/v6.6/dts/0009 + dts/0012).
#
# HOST-MODE BUILD (B-19 Stage C, WiFi plan Stage 1): dts/0012 switches the
# ssusb node to dr_mode="otg" + role-switch-default-mode="host" with an
# xhci-mtk child. That needs USB_MTU3_DUAL_ROLE (which Kconfig-requires
# USB_GADGET=y and EXTCON=y even though extcon is unused — role-switch takes
# priority, see ssusb_otg_switch_init()) and USB_XHCI_MTK. g_ether stays
# built in but is inert while the role defaults to host.
#
# VBUS chain (live-proven, boot.md "B-19 Stage C Phase 0"): FUSB301 CC
# controller on i2c1 in SOURCE mode (TYPEC_FUSB301A, patches/v6.6/usb/0001)
# + BQ25896 OTG boost regulator (CHARGER_BQ25890 + REGULATOR, IRQ-optional
# via patches/v6.6/power/0001) + GPIO107 hog in the DTS.
CONFIG_USB_MTU3=y
CONFIG_USB_MTU3_DUAL_ROLE=y
CONFIG_PHY_MTK_TPHY=y
CONFIG_USB_GADGET=y
CONFIG_USB_ETH=y
CONFIG_EXTCON=y
CONFIG_USB_ROLE_SWITCH=y
CONFIG_USB_XHCI_HCD=y
CONFIG_USB_XHCI_MTK=y
CONFIG_TYPEC=y
CONFIG_TYPEC_FUSB301A=y
CONFIG_REGULATOR=y
CONFIG_CHARGER_BQ25890=y
# USB mass-storage + usbnet basics so Gate G1a devices (SD reader,
# MediaTek USB-C ethernet adapter) actually bind once they enumerate.
CONFIG_USB_STORAGE=y
CONFIG_SCSI=y
CONFIG_BLK_DEV_SD=y
CONFIG_USB_USBNET=y
CONFIG_USB_NET_CDCETHER=y
CONFIG_USB_RTL8152=y
CONFIG_USB_NET_AX88179_178A=y
